<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4544.4.3>
    bibo:endPage "522" ;
    bibo:issue "4" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2019-01-15" ;
    bibo:startPage "505" ;
    bibo:volume "4544" ;
    dc:creator "Wang, Kai; Jiang, Ke; Ren, Jinlong; Zou, Dahu; Wu, Jiawei; Che, Jing; Siler, Cameron D." ;
    dc:date "2019" ;
    dc:title "A new species of Dwarf Japalura sensu lato (Reptilia: Squamata: Agamidae) from the upper Mekong River in Eastern Tibet, China, with notes on morphological variation, distribution, and conservation of two congeners along the same river" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618491>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618493>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618495>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618499>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618497>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618501> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618491>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Distribution of Japalura sensu lato in the Hengduan Mountain Region in Southwest China. Numbers represent new localities for Japalura vela (1–5) and J. iadina (6), which are: (1) Tongsha, Markam, Tibet; (2) Rumei Township, Markam Prefecture, Tibet; (3) Xilu, Deqin County, Yunnan Province; (4) Foshan, Deqin County, Yunnan Province; (5) Xidang, Deqin County, Yunnan Province; and (6) Yunling, Deqin County, Yunnan Province." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2618491/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618493>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Holotype male (left; KIZ 027619) and paratopotype female (right, KIZ 027617) of Japalura drukdaypo sp. nov. in life. Photos by Kai WANG." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2618493/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618495>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Dorsal (1), ventral (2), and lateral close-up (3) comparisons of male Japalura drukdaypo sp. nov. (holotype KIZ 027619) and J. vela (KIZ 027670), showing the relatively shorter tail, shorter hind limbs, smoother ventral scales, and feeble and non-erecting crest of J. drukdaypo sp. nov. compared with the closely distributed population of J. vela from Tongsha, Markam Prefecture, Tibet, China. Images are not to scale. Photos by Kai WANG." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2618495/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618499>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Comparisons of live males (columns 1, 2) and females (columns 3, 4) among Japalura drukdaypo sp. nov. (row A), J. batangensis (row B), J. vela (row C), J. laeviventris (row D), and J. flaviceps (row E). Photos by Kai WANG and Xu ZHANG." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2618499/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618497>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Dorsal (1) and ventral (2) comparisons of females among Japalura drukdaypo sp. nov. (paratopotype KIZ 027617), J. brevicauda (paratype ZMB 28932), and J. vela (KIZ 027671), showing the differences in relative tail length, relative limb length, and texture of ventral body scales. Individual images are not to scale. Dorsal view of J. vela (B1) was horizontally rotated 180˚ to align with other figures. Photos by Kai WANG and Frank TILLACK." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2618497/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2618501>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Habitat at the type localities of Japalura drukdaypo sp. nov. in Kanuo (A and B) and Chaya (C and D), Chamdo, Tibet, China. Photos by Kai WANG." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2618501/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

